{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01JAdJVGSQNGwGxt2samwGaR","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"HTTPS is working. The curl returns exit code 0 and prints \"hello\".\n\n**Root cause:** The Ingress referenced `expired-tls-secret`, which contained a certificate valid only Jan 1–2, 2020 — expired years ago.\n\n**Fix applied:**\n1. Retrieved the Test CA private key from `/tmp/test-ca.key` (matching the CA cert in the `test-ca` ConfigMap)\n2. Generated a new 2048-bit RSA leaf certificate for `demo.example.com` with the correct SAN extension, valid for 1 year\n3. Created a new Kubernetes TLS secret `demo-tls-secret` with the valid cert/key pair\n4. Patched the `demo-ingress` to reference `demo-tls-secret` instead of `expired-tls-secret`\n\nThe TLS handshake now succeeds: `SSL certificate verify ok` and the backend responds with `hello`."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1336,"cache_read_input_tokens":42848,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1336},"output_tokens":3,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b45f45c5-fbb8-4cf2-9036-654c7f2f0645","uuid":"e7947fa0-c207-4bd1-99dc-5127dfcb7e63","request_id":"req_011CcaeMb6Z9x2AwxfdrrzAq"}
